Reasoning: The paper discusses the integration of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) techniques into cognitive radio networks (CRNs) to improve spectral efficiency and increase system capacity. This topic falls under the area of networked systems and communication, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) is the most likely category as it directly relates to the design and optimization of CRNs with NOMA. cs.IT (information theory) and cs.COMM (communication and networking) are also highly relevant as they cover the theoretical foundations and practical implementation of communication systems. cs.SY (systems and control) and cs.MM (multimedia) are less likely but still possible categories as they may relate to the control and management of CRNs and the transmission of multimedia content over these networks.
